body:
WARNING: RANT

At least know how animals work. 

So this girl I was talking to today told me about how she went to Chick-Fil-A and saw some blackbirds eating some unfinished chicken sandwiches in the outside trash. 

Then she&#039;s all like, &quot;this is terrible; it&#039;s like we&#039;re encouraging cannibalism by throwing our food out like that.&quot; 

So I&#039;m all like, &quot;it&#039;s not cannibalism; they&#039;re two entirely different species.&quot;

And she&#039;s like, &quot;no, it&#039;s not. A chicken is a bird.&quot;

I didn&#039;t argue with her after that because, y&#039;know, I hate dealing with other people&#039;s bullshit. But, a blackbird eating some chicken is the same as a person eating some beef. A human and a cow may share a class, Mammalia, but once it gets more specific in classification, they branch off into totally different areas. Same goes with a blackbird and a chicken. Or a fox and a rabbit. Or a ladybug and aphids. Yes, I do agree that wild animals eating humans&#039; leftovers can be bad for their health and their survival, but please understand why something is bad with the right reason.
